{"questionId":"13468","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Steffi the stray cat often visits Will’s house in search of food. Let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n</math></span> be the discrete random&nbsp;variable “the number of times per day that Steffi visits Will’s house”.</p>\n<p>The random variable <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n</math></span> can be modelled by a Poisson distribution with mean 2.1.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let<em> Y</em> be the discrete random variable “the number of times per day that Steffi is fed at Will’s&nbsp;house”. Steffi is only fed on the first four occasions that she visits each day.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence find the expected number of times per day that Steffi is fed at Will’s house.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( Y \\right) = \\sum {y{\\text{P}}\\left( {Y = y} \\right)} \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>Y</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>∑</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi>y</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>P</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>(</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>Y</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>y</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = 1 \\times 0.257 \\ldots&nbsp; + 2 \\times 0.270 \\ldots&nbsp; + 3 \\times 0.189 + 4 \\times 0.161 \\ldots \">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>0.257</mn>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>0.270</mn>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>0.189</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>0.161</mn>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = 2.01\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2.01</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13468","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_10c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the expected number of times per day that Steffi is fed at Will’s house.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.17—Poisson distribution"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}